	     Cape Town – One person was seriously injured in a
paragliding accident in Green Point, Cape Town, on Monday.  City of Cape Town fire and rescue services spokesperson,
Theo Layne, said the paraglider crashed in Beach Road, Green Point, on Monday
afternoon. She was assisted by paramedics and fire rescue
services.  She was stabilised at the scene before she was
transported to the Christiaan Barnard Hospital. She was in a serious condition,
he said. No further information on the accident was available at
this point, he said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  